      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LOCHINVAR JAG (2) made it two wins on on the trot last start when he drew widest but had enough speed to find the front before going on to score by 1.4 metres at Menangle. Led from this barrier when winning a higher-graded race at Penrith prior. Should get every chance to land the hat trick. CERISE RAINBOW (6) draws wider but is hard to knock, placing in her last two outings at Menangle to follow back-to-back Penrith wins. MATT GREGORS BOY (5) had some decent city form last time in. Strikes at 50 per cent when fresh and should be forward enough following three trials, winning the latest. RICK REILLY NZ (4) is a newcomer to the Seaton Grima yard from Victoria and brings decent form, last time finishing 4.5 metres away in third in a higher-graded race at Melton. Keep safe.",
